Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We extend a warm welcome\Nto all who accepted an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to join us for this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.93,0:00:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in an unfriendly world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.10,0:00:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where true friends are hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to draw close to God\Nand have him as our Friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.94,0:00:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, what must we do\Nto gain God’s friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Kenneth Cook,\Na member of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.20,0:00:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will answer those questions\Nin the discourse entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.45,0:00:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Friendship With God—How Possible?”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.75,0:01:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it realistic to believe\Nthat you can be a friend of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If until now you’ve answered no\Nto that question,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.26,0:01:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,please consider this:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The lives of millions of people today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.93,0:01:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,prove that friendship with God is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.39,0:01:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Their lives prove that we can find\Na peaceful and meaningful life now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.15,0:01:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as hope\Nfor an everlasting and peaceful future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.86,0:01:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you desire that for yourself and others,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.87,0:01:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we urge you\Nto listen to this Scriptural talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.87,0:01:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We emphasize the need to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.12,0:01:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because many people ignore\Nthat important question,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.54,0:01:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, Can you be a friend of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.84,0:01:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it that many put\Nsuch an important question out of their mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a number of reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.89,0:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, some believe\Nthat God is impersonal or unknowable
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he does not exist\Nand that he’s not interested in humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.81,0:02:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They are taught that God is a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.19,0:02:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he’s cruel, harsh, and demanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.53,0:02:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Many religious leaders claim\Nthat God will punish bad people forever
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.66,0:02:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in a place of torment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel drawn into friendship\Nwith a God like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in their right mind would?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.83,0:02:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Still other people, after seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.83,0:02:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the injustice and suffering\Nin the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.71,0:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,have concluded that God must be dead
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he never existed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.39,0:02:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there are those who believe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.43,0:02:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have done\Ntoo many bad things in their life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.89,0:02:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to ever be a friend of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do any of those causes for doubt or concern\Napply to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, please listen carefully\Nto the following four key points
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.45,0:02:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that may help you to see\Nthat friendship with God is truly possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We will then develop each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.29,0:03:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we’ll look at how sin\Nseparates us from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.29,0:03:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we’ll look at how God\Nhas taken the initiative to heal the breach
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.30,0:03:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring obedient humans\Nback into friendship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.80,0:03:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we’ll examine what we can do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.55,0:03:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to become God’s friend in an everlasting way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we will consider\Nhow friendship with God
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,brings peace now and in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.81,0:03:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So for our first point:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.40,0:03:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that separates us from God?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In a word, sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does sin separate us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the true God is holy, he’s pure,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.41,0:03:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and his conduct is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.96,0:03:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He does not have a trace of sin;\Nhe’s clean in the highest sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.80,0:03:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No human can be holy to that degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate: Consider the words\N“human” and “imperfect.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.72,0:04:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They go together, don’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.35,0:04:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot fully describe humans\Nwithout mentioning imperfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just a part of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and human history shows this\Nto be sadly and painfully true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.11,0:04:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So then our sins or imperfections
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,create a barrier between us and God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.24,0:04:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This separation is described
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.45,0:04:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at Isaiah 59:2,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,where we are told in part:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.29,0:04:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your own errors have separated you\Nfrom your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.84,0:04:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sins have made him\Nhide his face from you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.84,0:04:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Separated from God,’ it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.76,0:04:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We were born into this state,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but God did not create us to be sinful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.27,0:04:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sins are not his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.98,0:04:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The first humans, Adam and Eve,\Nwere created perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But they proved to be ungrateful and selfish,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:04:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rejected God’s friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They destroyed their peace with God\Nby sinning against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.96,0:05:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they became his enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.21,0:05:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam then passed sin on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.79,0:05:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to his descendants, as well as death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.67,0:05:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We read about this terrible inheritance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.88,0:05:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 5:12.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.35,0:05:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In this verse, the apostle Paul summarizes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.43,0:05:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,why our inherited sinful condition\Nleads to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.10,0:05:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote:\N“That is why, just as through one man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.27,0:05:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“sin entered into the world\Nand death through sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.24,0:05:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“and so death spread to all men
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.70,0:05:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had all sinned.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.66,0:05:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Death spread to all men.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.75,0:05:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This pandemic of sin
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.83,0:05:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has a 100 percent infection rate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and a 100 percent mortality rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.84,0:05:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No human can escape it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.05,0:05:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As Paul said: “Death spread . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.59,0:05:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had all sinned.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.97,0:06:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,On our own,\Nwe cannot correct our sinful state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.89,0:06:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s as if we have fallen into a deep pit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.69,0:06:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with seemingly no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.23,0:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But are we left without hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.11,0:06:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, although God views some people\Nas his enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he treats others as his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.91,0:06:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, regarding the man Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible book of James\Nsays in chapter 2 and verse 23
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.04,0:06:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that “Abraham put faith in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.17,0:06:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it was counted to him as righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he came to be called Jehovah’s friend.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.14,0:06:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham was as imperfect as we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but he came to be called God’s friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.56,0:06:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What has God done\Nto make it possible for humans
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.60,0:06:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to gain his favor and blessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.98,0:06:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply put, our Creator\Nhas taken the initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.45,0:06:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He has taken steps to heal the breach\Nthat was caused by sin
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.45,0:07:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and to eliminate the separation\Nbetween us and him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.66,0:07:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How has he done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.71,0:07:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the Holy Scriptures tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.42,0:07:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that God desires for us to come to know him\Nand to be at peace with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he appeals to us to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible book of Acts 17:27,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we are told that God wants us\Nto sincerely seek him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and that if we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.85,0:07:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we will find that “he is not far off\Nfrom each one of us.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.61,0:07:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, and very important,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.82,0:07:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,God took the initiative to make this possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.86,0:07:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,by providing the sacrifice of his Son, Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to redeem us from sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.70,0:07:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an unparalleled act of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.71,0:07:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As we now read 1 John 4:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.71,0:07:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,please think about what it says
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.71,0:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding this matchless act of love\Non God’s part
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we may never forget\Nthat God took the initiative
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to heal the breach, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.93,0:08:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First John 4:10 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.23,0:08:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“The love is in this respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.81,0:08:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“not that we have loved God,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“but that he loved us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and sent his Son as a propitiatory sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for our sins.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.99,0:08:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What did God do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.99,0:08:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“God . . . loved us,” it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“and [he] sent his Son.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This sacrifice that God provided\Nby means of his Son
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.54,0:08:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is called “propitiatory”\Nbecause it can atone for our sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is how it can do so:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.59,0:08:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What Jesus gave in sacrifice for us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was equal to what Adam lost for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, a perfect human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.73,0:08:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam exchanged his perfect life for death
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.61,0:08:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by his rebellion against God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.44,0:08:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As mentioned earlier, Adam then\Npassed sin on to his descendants,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.45,0:09:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and he placed us on a path\Noutside of God’s friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.20,0:09:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Nthe death of Jesus allowed for a ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.04,0:09:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or a means to satisfy God’s justice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could receive back\Nwhat Adam lost for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.46,0:09:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That undeserved gift from God\Nwas given at great cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.97,0:09:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, our Creator wants us\Nto come to know him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.43,0:09:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and to enjoy a beautiful friendship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.31,0:09:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be very grateful\Nthat God took the necessary step
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to close the gap\Nand provide a way for us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.11,0:09:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to become his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.40,0:09:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The next step involves each of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.86,0:09:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is required of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.87,0:09:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.99,0:09:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We must be humble enough\Nto accept God’s gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.08,0:09:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are humble, we’ll see\Nour need for God’s mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.46,0:09:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll then do our part\Nto show appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible book of Acts 3:19 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.84,0:10:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that this involves\N‘repenting and turning around.’
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.60,0:10:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, to receive God’s gift,\Nwhich includes his mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.02,0:10:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we must adjust our thinking by repenting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.44,0:10:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and then turn around\Nby adjusting our conduct and course in life
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.69,0:10:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The opportunity to do this\Nis open to all people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.12,0:10:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As our Creator,\NGod is not partial in his mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.33,0:10:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the friendship he offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He has kindly put everything in place for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All we must do is be grateful and humble
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.30,0:10:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That step involves accepting Jesus\Nand his teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.14,0:10:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God requires that we follow\Nthe example of his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.48,0:10:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How closely must we do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.89,0:10:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 14:6, Jesus explained:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am the way and the truth and the life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No one comes to the Father\Nexcept through me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.99,0:11:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“No one.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.74,0:11:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, to come into God’s friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.12,0:11:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we must follow his Son as true Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.38,0:11:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, we have reviewed\Nhow sin separated humans from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.38,0:11:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we considered what God has done\Nto heal the breach, or close the gap,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.22,0:11:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can come back\Ninto his favor as his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.64,0:11:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s look even further\Ninto what we must do,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which brings us to the third key point:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.77,0:11:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How can a person become God’s friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to consider what is said
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.65,0:11:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at James 4:8.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a copy of the Bible,\Nwe urge you to follow along
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.70,0:11:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—James 4:8.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.37,0:11:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read it,\Nplease notice first the invitation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then the response,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.67,0:11:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally what we must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.67,0:12:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Draw close to God,\Nand he will draw close to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.35,0:12:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cleanse your hands, you sinners,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.56,0:12:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and purify your hearts, you indecisive ones.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.73,0:12:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first, what is the invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.07,0:12:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It is to “draw close to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.15,0:12:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That is followed\Nby what response on God’s part?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will draw close to you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But for God to do this, what must we do
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.95,0:12:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to show that we accept his invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We must cleanse and purify ourselves\Naccording to his standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This will take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.71,0:12:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nwe must learn about his standards,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.67,0:12:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we must come to appreciate\Nthat they are the best for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.47,0:12:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we must be determined\Nto follow them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.43,0:12:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Above all, we do this\Nbecause we want to please God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.23,0:12:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, how can you develop\Na friendship with God?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.53,0:13:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Show initiative and put forth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider this: If you have a houseplant,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.28,0:13:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that it doesn’t grow on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.99,0:13:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to water it regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep it in an environment\Nthat helps it to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,True?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Something similar is true\Nof our friendship with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We nurture this friendship by reading\Nand studying God’s Word, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do so,\Nwe learn important things about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.26,0:13:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nwe learn that God’s name is Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And as is true of any good friendship,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.98,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s important that we use his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re sincere in our efforts\Nto “draw close” to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.57,0:13:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as we read at James 4:8,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.49,0:13:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will “draw close” to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.82,0:13:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And he never abandons his true friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, John 17:3 tells us\Nthat coming to know God
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.21,0:13:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“means everlasting life” for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.29,0:14:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What an undeserved kindness\Nand priceless gift
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.22,0:14:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s true friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.18,0:14:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you too can enjoy\Na bright future as God’s friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.26,0:14:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we warmly invite you to accept\Na free interactive Bible course
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.10,0:14:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,offered by Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,using the publication {\i1}{s16}{nArial}Enjoy life Forever! 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.23,0:14:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.74,0:14:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses can help you\Nto get either a printed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.37,0:14:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or an electronic copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.99,0:14:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins with the lessons:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.29,0:14:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“How Can the Bible Help You?”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Bible Gives Hope,”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and “Can You Trust the Bible?”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We urge you to learn these things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.21,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and to worship God in harmony with the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that is revealed in his Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.30,0:14:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what important points have we considered
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding how a person\Ncan become God’s friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.35,0:14:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First, get to know God\Nby reading and studying his Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.94,0:15:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that doing this\N“means everlasting life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.49,0:15:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,learn about God’s name and use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.74,0:15:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we’ll list four more things
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that those who desire\Nto become God’s friends must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They are: imitate God’s qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.29,0:15:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,reject thinking and actions that offend God,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,associate with those\Nwho want to be God’s friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.76,0:15:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoid friendship with people
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who ignore or mock God’s standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.39,0:15:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a few things in that list\Nspeak for themselves—don’t they?—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.68,0:15:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,such as associate with those\Nwho want to be God’s friend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.44,0:15:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoid friendship with people\Nwho ignore or mock God’s standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.44,0:15:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes sense, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.15,0:15:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Think back to our illustration\Nabout the houseplant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.91,0:15:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You must not only water and nurture it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.45,0:15:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but you must keep it\Nin the right environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,one that helps it to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.46,0:15:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, associating with those\Nwho also want to be God’s friend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.88,0:16:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the right environment for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about the requirement\Nto imitate God’s qualities?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How can imperfect people do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.39,0:16:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for a few minutes,\Nwe’ll look at just two of God’s qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we can imitate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.44,0:16:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will begin with God’s love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.61,0:16:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,An important way that we can imitate\NGod’s love and become his friend
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.69,0:16:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is by applying what his Son, Jesus,\Ntaught us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.03,0:16:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.12,0:16:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just as you want men to do to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.04,0:16:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do the same way to them”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—a simple statement\Nbut one that takes effort to apply, true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.54,0:16:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.92,0:16:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.92,0:16:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And a person who desires to be God’s friend
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.67,0:16:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,will put forth the effort needed to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.09,0:16:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To succeed in imitating God’s love,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.18,0:16:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we must try to see people\Nas Jehovah sees them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.27,0:16:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We must try to put ourselves\Nin the place of others
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.39,0:17:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can understand\Ntheir needs, their concerns,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.19,0:17:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and even their pain of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.86,0:17:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some may be challenged physically\Nbecause of injury, disease, or aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Others are coping with emotional trials
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because of depression or anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.66,0:17:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people face difficulties\Nthat we have not experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, a young person\Nmay find it hard
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.29,0:17:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand older people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.80,0:17:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and he or she will really need to think\Nabout what it must be like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.09,0:17:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to be an older person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.47,0:17:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is true of you,\Nhow can you imitate God’s love?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.43,0:17:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,One important way is by listening carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.89,0:17:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,until you understand\Nthe other person’s feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do so, you are in a better position
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.57,0:17:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to imitate God’s love.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.15,0:17:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who desire to be Jehovah’s friends
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.99,0:17:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will be moved to imitate his love
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.53,0:17:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by acting according\Nto what others really need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:17:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings us to a second\Nand related quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.33,0:18:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.34,0:18:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who desires to be God’s friend\Nmust be kind to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.09,0:18:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Here again, we can learn much\Nfrom what Jesus said and did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.51,0:18:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Son said that the Most High
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.22,0:18:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“is kind toward the unthankful and wicked.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.10,0:18:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus appreciated this outstanding quality\Nof his heavenly Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.36,0:18:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and he imitated God’s kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.53,0:18:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped Jesus to do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.57,0:18:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He treated people in a kind manner
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,by anticipating how his words and actions
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.45,0:18:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might affect their feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.79,0:18:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the Bible tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that a woman known to be a sinner\Napproached Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.17,0:18:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,weeping and wetting his feet with her tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.51,0:18:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus discerned that she was repentant,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.63,0:18:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knew how heartbroken she would be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.30,0:18:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,if he just dismissed her unkindly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like his heavenly Father,\NJesus looked for the good in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.10,0:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We know this because he commended her;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.27,0:19:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then he forgave her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.65,0:19:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Following Jesus’ example,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.65,0:19:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we also imitate God’s kindness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.45,0:19:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do so by being gentle to all people\Nwhenever possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind people discern\Nhow to deal with delicate situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind people avoid hurting\Nthe feelings of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.09,0:19:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do this, we try to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.51,0:19:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how our words and actions might affect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.76,0:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is how a true friend of God\Nwill treat others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.64,0:19:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this review of just a few\Nof Jehovah’s many outstanding qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.02,0:19:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us an idea of how much we can benefit\Nfrom reading the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then applying its many lessons for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, friendship with God is possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.62,0:19:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can imitate his outstanding qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.33,0:20:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following video,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.33,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,please take note of how we can use the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to build a friendship with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.14,0:20:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever wanted to ask God:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.60,0:20:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.73,0:20:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.77,0:20:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you care about me?”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people everywhere have felt the need
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.91,0:20:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to know their Maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.62,0:20:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a woman\Nwho has never known her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All her life she has been told lies\Nthat her father abandoned her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But deep inside she feels\N—she knows—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.48,0:21:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,One day,\Nshe receives a letter from her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.86,0:21:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She learns that he is alive\Nand that, unbeknownst to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he had been reaching out\Nto be part of her life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.41,0:21:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,since the day she was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The daughter learns who her father is,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.09,0:21:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.26,0:21:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,she finds him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.82,0:21:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They learn about one another
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.16,0:21:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a strong bond
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.79,0:22:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,until they are inseparable friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.21,0:22:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible is like a group
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of letters from our heavenly Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.30,0:22:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.51,0:22:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn how to talk to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.97,0:22:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how he responds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.23,0:22:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the many ways
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.35,0:22:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,he shows his tender care.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.57,0:22:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible can help us to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.74,0:22:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we may never have thought possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.87,0:22:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—be God’s friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That friendship starts by learning the name
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.79,0:22:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of your heavenly Father and new Friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.63,0:22:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and God tells us his name:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“You, whose name is Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.93,0:22:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you alone are the Most High.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.60,0:23:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah guarantees that if you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.35,0:23:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘draw close to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.82,0:23:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he will draw close to you.’
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our loving Father openly extends friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.95,0:23:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to all who search for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.53,0:23:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you accept his invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.79,0:23:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more about what the Bible says
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.25,0:23:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on this and many other topics,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.84,0:23:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,go to jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.35,0:23:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As that thought-provoking video asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.77,0:23:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,do you see the need\Nto come to know your Creator?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.02,0:23:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you willing to put forth\Nthe effort needed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.53,0:23:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept his invitation\Nand become his friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.15,0:23:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, the Bible contains\Nthe guidance that you need,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.16,0:24:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reward for applying what it says
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.08,0:24:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is not reserved for the future only.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.08,0:24:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Friendship with God brings peace now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.59,0:24:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a more peaceful\Nand meaningful life right now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.72,0:24:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by becoming Jehovah’s friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When you become a friend of God,\Nhe will listen to your prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.39,0:24:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and extend his mercy to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.85,0:24:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you sense his forgiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.02,0:24:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you will experience deep-seated joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.19,0:24:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 32:1, 2 says in part:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.23,0:24:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the one\Nwhose transgression is pardoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.57,0:24:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“whose sin is covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.45,0:24:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy is the man\Nwhom Jehovah does not charge with guilt.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.95,0:24:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blessing it is\Nto sense Jehovah’s forgiveness!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.83,0:24:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s forgiveness can free you\Nfrom the burden of guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.46,0:24:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you may feel because of past wrongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.76,0:24:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This includes wrongs\Nthat you may have committed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.05,0:24:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,before you came to know God\Nand became his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.72,0:25:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is such a thing possible for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.89,0:25:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.89,0:25:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As our video pointed out,\Nthe Bible teaches us how to pray to God
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.44,0:25:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and how God responds to our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.65,0:25:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can be assured\Nthat he will listen to your prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.40,0:25:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,including your prayers\Nfor his forgiveness and his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.66,0:25:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,At Proverbs 15:29 we read
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.33,0:25:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah\N“hears the prayer of the righteous.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.71,0:25:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the righteous?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.71,0:25:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The righteous are those who strive\Nto live by his requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.63,0:25:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What a comfort for us to know\Nthat we can be God’s friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.34,0:25:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because he sees what we are trying to do
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.39,0:25:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and he listens to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.56,0:25:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.56,0:25:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our friendship with God can also result\Nin peace with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.31,0:25:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jesus urged us\Nto seek such peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.94,0:25:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that we should ‘love even our enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.78,0:25:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and do good to others\Nwithout hoping for anything back.’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.87,0:26:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we read at Luke 6:36 that he added:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.16,0:26:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue being merciful,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.25,0:26:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,just as your Father is merciful.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.75,0:26:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a good example\Ncan touch the hearts of others
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.09,0:26:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and move them\Nto become Jehovah’s friends as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.97,0:26:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the experience of José,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.68,0:26:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who learned how to love\Nfrom true friends of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.56,0:26:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At the age of 13, José was involved\Nin guerrilla warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.06,0:26:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was taught to hate the people\Nwho were allegedly responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.36,0:26:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for the injustices\Nthat he saw all around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.24,0:26:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,His aim was to eliminate those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.74,0:26:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw many of his companions fall in death,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.41,0:26:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and José became filled\Nwith feelings of bitterness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.79,0:26:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.79,0:26:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,While making grenades or bombs,\Nhe would ask himself:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.46,0:26:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why is there so much suffering?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.76,0:26:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a God, does he even notice?’
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.84,0:27:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times, José wept.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.22,0:27:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He was depressed and confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.35,0:27:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, José came in contact
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.64,0:27:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with a local congregation\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.11,0:27:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At his first congregation meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.52,0:27:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he noticed the loving atmosphere there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.36,0:27:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone greeted him\Nin a warm and friendly manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.03,0:27:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, a discussion on the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.91,0:27:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why Does God Permit Wickedness?”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.58,0:27:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,provided answers to the very questions\Nthat he had been asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.12,0:27:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As he learned more from the Bible,\NJosé made changes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.29,0:27:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in his way of life and in his thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.96,0:27:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He learned to imitate God’s love
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.34,0:27:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby become his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.05,0:27:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Breaking his ties with his companions,\Nthough, proved to be challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.27,0:27:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time he went\Nto the Kingdom Hall of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.60,0:27:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he was followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.60,0:27:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Some former associates\Neven attended a few meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.73,0:27:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to understand what brought about\Nsuch a great change in José.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.24,0:27:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But once they were satisfied\Nthat he was not a danger to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.82,0:28:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they left him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.83,0:28:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At age 17, José was baptized\Nas one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.50,0:28:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As God’s friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.50,0:28:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,José soon started sharing\Nwhat he was learning full-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.50,0:28:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of scheming to kill people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.13,0:28:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he could now share a message\Nof love and of hope with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.47,0:28:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great reward for choosing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.18,0:28:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to become Jehovah’s friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.93,0:28:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, even those who were once enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.19,0:28:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can learn to be at peace with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.98,0:28:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and be God’s friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.77,0:28:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what have we learned?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.78,0:28:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We have reviewed why friendship with God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.07,0:28:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is realistic and possible for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.45,0:28:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible tells us that since ancient times,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.62,0:28:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God has called some humans his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.00,0:28:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We also looked at what God has done
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.04,0:28:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to heal the breach, or close the gap,\Nbetween us and him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.21,0:28:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How has he done so?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of his Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.55,0:29:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Through Jesus, Jehovah God provided\Nthe ransom sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.10,0:29:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that was needed to redeem us from sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.52,0:29:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we looked at what you must do\Nto take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.27,0:29:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s mercy and become his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.86,0:29:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This includes studying his Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.02,0:29:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then imitating his outstanding qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.07,0:29:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we considered
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.28,0:29:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can find a meaningful life now,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as true peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.79,0:29:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah promises that his friends
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.71,0:29:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,will receive eternal life in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.09,0:29:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is what you yearn for,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.55,0:29:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,then please accept our invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.01,0:29:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the Bible with Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.05,0:29:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing so, you will learn\Nabout an unending future
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.27,0:29:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when anguish of heart is gone forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.40,0:29:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an unending future
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.52,0:29:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in which God will permanently\Nwipe away tears
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.69,0:29:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the faces of his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.32,0:30:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That future is not only possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.78,0:30:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the future that God promises!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.29,0:30:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Cook,\Nfor helping us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.62,0:30:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how friendship with God\Nleads to genuine peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.88,0:30:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the earth, millions are pursuing peace
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.51,0:30:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and building faith in Jehovah God\Nand his Word, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.68,0:30:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would like to have Bible discussions,\Nfree of charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.97,0:30:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time and place convenient for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.52,0:30:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,please inform one of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.35,0:30:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or visit jw.org
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.44,0:30:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and fill out an online request\Nfor a Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.74,0:30:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be happy to arrange\Nfor one of Jehovah’s Witnesses to assist you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.70,0:30:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, you can find
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.74,0:30:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive, self-guided Bible study lessons
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.62,0:30:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on our website, jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.17,0:30:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have reached the conclusion\Nof this session.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.17,0:30:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to the next session\Nin which we will see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.30,0:31:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,part two of our feature Bible drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.22,0:31:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s16}{nArial}“Jehovah Guides Us in the Way of Peace{
},”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.01,0:31:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will hear the final talk\Nof this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.14,0:31:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s sing a song\Nthat expresses our confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.27,0:31:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in God’s promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.27,0:31:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to sing\Nsong number 147, entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.28,0:31:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Life Everlasting Is Promised.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.36,0:31:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s song number 147,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.12,0:31:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,after which you may have\Nyour local concluding prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.71,0:00:26.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,招待に応じてこの大会を\N視聴してくださっている皆さんを
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.59,0:00:29.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,温かく歓迎いたします
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:35.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,今の世の中で本当の友達を\N見つけるのは簡単ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:39.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神と親しくなって友達に\Nなることはできるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.94,0:00:44.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしできるとしたら\N何をすればよいのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:48.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体の成員 ケニス･クック兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.19,0:00:52.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,講演の中でそうした点に\N答えてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.49,0:00:56.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は 「神と友達になるには」です
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.69,0:01:09.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と友達になることなんて\Nできないと思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.24,0:01:11.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう思っている皆さんに
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:14.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひ知っていただきたい点があります
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.45,0:01:17.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 何百万人もの人たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:20.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に神と友達になっています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.58,0:01:25.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人たちは平和で充実した毎日を送り
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:29.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも平和に暮らせる\Nという希望を持っています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.88,0:01:32.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分もそうなりたいと思うなら
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.18,0:01:36.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひ聖書に基づくこの話を\N聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.68,0:01:39.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ聞いていただきたいかというと
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.27,0:01:44.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人は神の友達になれるのか\Nという重要な質問について
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.23,0:01:46.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えようとしないからです
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.98,0:01:50.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人がこのことを\N気に留めないのはなぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.99,0:01:52.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,理由はさまざまです
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.03,0:01:57.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人たちは 神なんて\N遠い存在だと考えています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:02:01.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はいないとか 人間には\N関心がないと言う人もいます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:05.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は謎めいていて 残酷で 厳しくて
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.46,0:02:08.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,要求ばかりすると言う人もいます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.71,0:02:14.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの宗教では 神が悪人を永遠の\N責め苦に遭わせると教えています
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.14,0:02:18.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような神と友達に\Nなりたいと思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.06,0:02:21.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,とてもそうは思えないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.19,0:02:26.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人たちは 世の中の\N不公正や苦しみを見て
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.69,0:02:29.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は死んでしまったに違いないとか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.28,0:02:32.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めからいなかったんだと言います
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:36.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人たちは 自分は悪いことを\Nたくさんしてしまったので
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:41.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になんてなれないと\N思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.66,0:02:45.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたもそんなふうに\N思ったことがありますか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:48.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそうなら この話は\Nきっと役立つでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.71,0:02:50.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,4つの点を考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.76,0:02:54.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分も神と友達になれると\N思えるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.68,0:02:57.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,では考えていきましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.22,0:03:02.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つ目に 私たちを神から\N引き離したのは罪です
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.31,0:03:07.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目に 神は人間のために\N自分の方から行動し
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.69,0:03:11.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い関係を取り戻せるように\Nしてくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.86,0:03:16.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目に いつまでも\N神の友達でいるためには
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.16,0:03:18.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,しなければならないことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.83,0:03:21.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,4つ目に 神の友達になる人は
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.95,0:03:25.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も将来も平和を楽しめます
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.58,0:03:28.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,では1つ目の点を考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを神から引き離したのは\N何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:34.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,一言で言うと罪です
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.93,0:03:37.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそう言えますか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:41.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜなら 真の神は清く聖なる方で
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:43.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,行いが完全だからです
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪が全くなく 最高度に清い方です
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.77,0:03:54.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間は誰一人 神と同じほど\N聖なる状態になることはできません
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.78,0:03:58.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人間」と「不完全」という言葉に\Nついて考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:02.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間といえば不完全\N不完全といえば人間です
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:06.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間の歴史を見ると
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.00,0:04:10.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,その現実が痛いほどよく分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.17,0:04:15.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪や不完全さによって壁ができました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:18.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちと神との間にです
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.34,0:04:21.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは神から\N引き離されてしまったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.72,0:04:26.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,その点はイザヤ 59:2に\N書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.15,0:04:31.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたたちは自らの過ちによって\N神から引き離された⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:35.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちの罪のせいで\N神は顔を隠した」
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:38.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神から引き離された」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.87,0:04:41.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,生まれつきこういう状態です
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:44.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも私たちが罪人なのは
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:48.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間を造った神のせいではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:51.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の人アダムとエバは完全でした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.79,0:04:55.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも神への感謝を忘れて自分勝手になり
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.84,0:04:58.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との友情を失いました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:03.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に罪を犯したので 神と\N平和な関係でいられなくなり
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.22,0:05:05.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:07.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人から生まれた子孫は
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.73,0:05:10.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪と死を受け継ぎました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:13.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほどひどい結果になったかが
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.48,0:05:17.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 5:12に書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:22.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで使徒パウロは\N罪と死がどう関係しているのかを
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.24,0:05:26.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,短い言葉で説明しています\Nこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:30.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,「このような訳で 1人の人によって\N人類に罪が入り
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:33.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪によって死が入り
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:36.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうして全ての人が罪人になったために
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.84,0:05:40.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,死が全ての人に広がった」
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:43.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「死が全ての人に広が」りました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.64,0:05:45.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,この罪というパンデミックは
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.97,0:05:48.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,感染率が100パーセントです
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:51.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,死亡率も100パーセントです
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.81,0:05:53.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰も逃れられません
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.90,0:05:56.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,「全ての人が罪人になったために
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.69,0:06:00.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,死が⋯⋯広がった」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:03.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,自力ではこの状態から\N抜け出すことができません
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,深い穴の中に落ちて
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:09.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,出口が見えないようなものです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.25,0:06:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも希望がないわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.04,0:06:15.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は全ての人を敵と見ている\Nわけではないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.75,0:06:18.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の友と見ている人もいます
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.01,0:06:22.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 「ヤコブの手紙」 2:23は
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.89,0:06:26.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムという人について\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.14,0:06:29.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,「『アブラハムはエホバに信仰を持ち
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:32.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことは正しいと見なされた』⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:36.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムはエホバの友と\N呼ばれるようになったのです」
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.15,0:06:40.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,アブラハムは私たちと同様\N不完全でした
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.70,0:06:44.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 神の友と呼ばれる\Nようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.20,0:06:49.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,不完全な人間がどうして神の友達に\Nなることができるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.87,0:06:54.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,簡単に言うと 神の方から\N行動してくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:58.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちとの良い関係を\N取り戻すために行動し
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.46,0:07:02.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが神に近づけるように\Nしてくださったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.64,0:07:04.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:06.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず聖書によると
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.97,0:07:09.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は私たちがご自分を知り
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:12.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分との友情を育むことを\N望んでいます
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.60,0:07:15.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 そうするよう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.52,0:07:18.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒 17:27によると
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:24.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は私たちが神を誠実に\N知ろうとすることを願っています
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.37,0:07:30.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際「神は 私たち一人一人から\N遠く離れてはいません」
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:33.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,次はとても大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.33,0:07:35.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は自分の方から
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.88,0:07:39.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,子であるイエスを犠牲として\N与えてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.46,0:07:42.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを罪から自由にするためです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.88,0:07:47.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はこのようにして\N最大の愛を示してくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:52.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ第一 4:10を読みながら
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.19,0:07:57.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神がどれほど大きな愛を示してくれたか\Nについて考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:01.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちとの間にできた壁を取り除くため
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.15,0:08:04.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の方から行動してくれたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.32,0:08:07.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ第一 4:10
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.24,0:08:09.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私たちが神を愛したというより
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:12.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が私たちを愛し
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.46,0:08:18.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの罪を償う犠牲として\Nご自分の子を遣わしてくださったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:20.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそが愛です」
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.13,0:08:24.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神［は］私たちを愛し⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:27.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の子を遣わしてくださ」いました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:31.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は犠牲としてご自分の子を\N遣わしました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.60,0:08:35.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,その犠牲には罪を「償う」力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.02,0:08:38.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:41.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,アダムは完全な命を失いました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.61,0:08:44.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが犠牲として差し出したのも
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.49,0:08:47.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間としての完全な命です
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.99,0:08:51.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,アダムは神に反逆してしまったため
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.62,0:08:54.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,完全な命を失いました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.50,0:08:57.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果 アダムの子孫は
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.38,0:08:59.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪を代々受け継ぎ
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:04.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,神から引き離され\N神との友情を失ったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.30,0:09:07.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,贖いと呼ばれるイエスの犠牲には
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.30,0:09:10.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,アダムが失ったものを\N取り戻す力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.68,0:09:14.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の公正という基準に\Nかなっているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:18.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は大きな犠牲を払って\Nこの贈り物をしてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:22.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は私たちにご自分のことを\N知ってほしい
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.40,0:09:26.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,友達になってほしいと願っているのです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.41,0:09:30.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが神と親しくなり\N友達になれるよう
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.58,0:09:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の方から行動して
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,道を開いてくれたことを\Nうれしく思いませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.58,0:09:41.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目です\N私たちには何が求められますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.84,0:09:47.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜さです 神からの贈り物を\N謙遜に受け取る必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:51.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜であれば 神の憐れみが\N必要であることを認め
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.56,0:09:55.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,感謝を表すために\N精いっぱいのことを行うはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.98,0:09:59.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「使徒の活動」 3:19にある通り
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:04.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,「悔い改めて生き方を\N変え」なければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.65,0:10:09.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 憐れみを含む\N神からの贈り物を頂くには
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.07,0:10:12.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,悔い改めることによって考え方を変え
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.66,0:10:14.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,行いや生き方の点で
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.91,0:10:18.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要な変化を遂げなければ\Nならないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:22.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうする機会は\N全ての人に開かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.09,0:10:26.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者である神は\N全ての人に憐れみを示しています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:28.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,友達になりたいと思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.39,0:10:31.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのために必要なことを\N全部してくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.64,0:10:35.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちがすべきなのは\N感謝して 謙遜になり
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.39,0:10:38.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のことを行うことです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.44,0:10:43.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスとイエスの教えを\N受け入れることです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.11,0:10:47.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はイエスの手本に倣うようにと\N言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.40,0:10:50.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,どの程度倣うべきでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.07,0:10:54.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 14:6でイエスは\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:58.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は道であり 真理であり 命です
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:03.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,私を通してでなければ 誰も\N父のもとに行くことはできません」
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:07.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 神の友達になるには
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.30,0:11:11.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスにしっかり従う必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:17.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここまでで 人間が罪によって\N神から引き離されたこと
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:21.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,また私たちが神の友達になれるよう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:26.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,神がどのように壁を取り除いて\Nくださったかを考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:29.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,では次の点を考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.53,0:11:32.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは神の友達になるために
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.91,0:11:36.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,何をしなければならないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:42.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にヤコブ 4:8を開いて\N考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.50,0:11:46.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書をお持ちであれば\Nどうぞ目で追ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.67,0:11:49.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブ 4:8です
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.34,0:11:51.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の点に注目してください
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:54.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことが呼び掛けられているか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.43,0:11:56.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は何をしてくれるか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:01.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは何をすべきか です\Nこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:06.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神に近づいてください そうすれば\N神は近づいてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.36,0:12:08.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪人たち 手を清めてください
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.86,0:12:13.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,優柔不断な人たち\N心を清めてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.62,0:12:18.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず「神に近づいてください」と\N呼び掛けられています
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.08,0:12:21.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に近づくなら\N神は何をしてくれるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.71,0:12:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「近づいてくださいます」
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.21,0:12:26.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも神に近づいてもらうため
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.92,0:12:29.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,しなければならないことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.88,0:12:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の基準に従って
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:34.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を清めなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:37.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのためには努力が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.64,0:12:40.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の基準を学ばなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.89,0:12:44.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,その基準が一番\N良いものであることを信じ
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.44,0:12:48.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに従うことを決意\Nしなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.57,0:12:54.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に喜ばれたい 神の友達になりたい\Nという気持ちからそうします
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.28,0:12:58.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どうすれば神との友情を\N育てられるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.16,0:13:01.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,進んで行動し努力することです
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.16,0:13:03.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,植物を育てているとしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:05.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,植物には世話が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:11.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,定期的に水をやり 成長に適した環境を\N整えなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:16.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との友情を育てるためにも\N同じようなことが必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.47,0:13:21.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を学ぶことによって\N神との友情を育てることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:25.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書から神について\N大切なことを学べます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.44,0:13:29.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の名がエホバであることが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.11,0:13:31.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは友達を名前で呼びます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.99,0:13:35.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 神の名を使うことは大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.57,0:13:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブ 4:8に書かれている通り
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.66,0:13:42.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが神に「近づ」くために\N誠実に努力するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは「近づ」いてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.79,0:13:49.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 決して\N真の友を見捨てたりしません
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:52.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 17:3にある通り
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:54.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のことを知るなら
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.26,0:13:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,「永遠の命を得る」ことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.43,0:14:01.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはエホバが真の友に\N惜しみなく与える
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.64,0:14:04.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,貴重な贈り物です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.10,0:14:08.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたも神の友達になって\N幸せに暮らしたいと思いませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.44,0:14:13.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうであれば ぜひエホバの証人と\N無料の聖書レッスンを楽しんでください
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.86,0:14:20.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,テキストは「いつまでも幸せに\N暮らせます」という出版物です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:22.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,これです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:28.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人から印刷版や電子版を\N入手することができます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.92,0:14:32.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の3つのレッスンは\N「聖書はどのように役立つ？」
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:35.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖書を読むと希望が持てる」
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.26,0:14:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖書は信用できる本？」です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:41.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした点を学び
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.35,0:14:47.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,書かれている真理に沿って\N神を崇拝するようお勧めします
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:53.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここまでで 神の友達になるには\Nどうしたらよいかについて考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:57.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず聖書を学んで\N神について知ることです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:01.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは そうすれば\N「永遠の命を得」られると言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.66,0:15:06.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして神の名を知り 使うことです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:11.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になりたいと願う人が\Nしなければならないことは
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.13,0:15:13.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかにもあります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.21,0:15:15.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の性格に倣うこと
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.68,0:15:19.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が嫌うことを考えたり\N行ったりしないこと
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.01,0:15:23.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になりたい人と交友を持つこと
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:26.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の基準を無視したり\Nばかにしたりする人と
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.65,0:15:29.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,付き合わないようにすることです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,今挙げた中に 神の友達に\Nなりたい人との交友を持ち
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.15,0:15:37.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の基準を無視したり\Nばかにしたりする人と
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.07,0:15:39.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,付き合わないように\Nすることがありました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.53,0:15:42.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは当然ではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:45.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほどの植物の例えを\N思い出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:48.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,水や肥料をやるだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.46,0:15:53.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,植物が成長しやすい環境を\N整えなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:56.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにも良い環境が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.05,0:16:01.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのためには 神の友になりたい人を\N友にしなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:05.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神の性格に倣うことについては\Nどうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:08.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,不完全な私たちにできるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:11.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の性格の2つの特徴を取り上げ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.82,0:16:14.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように倣えるかを考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:18.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず愛について考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.61,0:16:22.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のような愛を身に着け\N神の友達になるには
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.70,0:16:26.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが教えたことを\N実践しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.08,0:16:28.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えばイエスはこう教えました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.79,0:16:33.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人からしてほしいと思う通りに\N人にもしなさい」
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:38.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンプルな教えですが\N実践するには努力が要ります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.68,0:16:41.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも不可能なことではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:43.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になりたいと思う人は
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.02,0:16:47.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのために一生懸命努力します
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.10,0:16:53.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の愛に倣うには 神のような愛情深い\Nまなざしで人々を見る必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.19,0:16:57.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,相手の身になって考え\N何を必要とし 何を心配し
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:17:02.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな心の痛みを抱えているかを\N理解するよう努めましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.74,0:17:05.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,けがや病気や老化のために
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.41,0:17:08.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい思いをしているかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.25,0:17:13.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,気分が落ち込んだり 心配事を\N抱えたりしている人もいることでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:17.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人にしか分からないような\N問題もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:23.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 若い人には高齢の人の気持ちが\Nなかなか分からないかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.05,0:17:25.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと考えただけでは\N年を取るというのが
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:28.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことか分からないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.60,0:17:33.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どうすれば神のような愛を\N身に着けられるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:37.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,高齢の人の気持ちがある程度\N理解できるようになるまで
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:40.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,話によく耳を傾けることです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:45.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 神のような愛を\N少しずつ身に着けられます
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:49.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの友達になりたいと\N思っている人は
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.12,0:17:55.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの愛に倣い 相手が本当に\N必要としている事柄を考えて行動します
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:18:01.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神の性格の2つ目の特徴である\N親切に注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.26,0:18:03.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になりたいと思う人は
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,人に親切でなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.26,0:18:10.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,この点についてもイエスの\N言動から多くを学べます
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:13.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは至高者である神が
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:17.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「感謝しない悪人にも\N親切」だと言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:21.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは天のお父さんエホバの\N親切に感動し
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:24.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じような親切を示しました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:27.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにそうしたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.66,0:18:31.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がこういうことを言ったら\Nあるいはこういうことをしたら
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:35.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,相手がどんな気持ちになるだろう と\Nよく考えたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:39.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 罪人として知られる女性が
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:42.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの所に来て 泣いて
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.22,0:18:45.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,涙でイエスの足をぬらし始めました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:49.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは彼女が悔い改めていることを\N見て取りました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:54.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして不親切にあしらったら\Nとても傷つくに違いないと思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:56.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,天のお父さんと同じように
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:18:59.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,この女性の良いところを見たのです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:02.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして彼女を褒め
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:05.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼女の罪を許しました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:11.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもどうすれば\N神の親切に倣えるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:13.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつでも誰にでも
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:16.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,優しく接することによってです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:21.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切な人は 相手の気持ちを\N察することができます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:24.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,相手の感情を傷つけないよう\N気を付けます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:27.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がこういうことを言ったら
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:31.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういうことをしたら相手は\Nどう思うだろうと考えるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:37.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達である人は\N人にそのように接します
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:41.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にエホバの愛と\N親切について考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.86,0:19:46.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,このように聖書を読んで\N学んだことを当てはめることは
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.82,0:19:50.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に私たちのためになります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.58,0:19:53.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と友達になることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.67,0:19:58.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の素晴らしい性格に\N近づくこともできます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:00.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を使ってどのように神との友情を\N育てることができるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:19.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神様にこう祈ったことがありますか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.73,0:20:23.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「もしおられるなら\Nどこにおられるのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,私のことを気に掛けてくれていますか」
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:30.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔から 世界中の多くの人が
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:36.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間を造った神について\N知りたいと思ってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:44.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,父親のことをよく知らない\N女性がいたとします
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:51.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたはお父さんに捨てられたのよ」\Nと言われて育ってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:21:00.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 心の中では「それは違う」\Nと感じていました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:07.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 父親から手紙が来ました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:14.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙を読んで お父さんは生きていて
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.75,0:21:17.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が生まれた時からずっと気に掛け
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.63,0:21:21.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けになりたいと思ってくれていた\Nことが分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:26.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして お父さんがどこにいるかも\N分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:35.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:38.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,会うことができました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:56.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いのことをよく知って
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.12,0:22:00.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,親友のような強い絆が生まれました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.38,0:22:09.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は お父さんともいえる\N神からの手紙のようなものです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.47,0:22:13.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むと
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.85,0:22:16.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,神にどのように祈れるか
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はどのように答えてくれるか
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:26.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちのことをどれほど気に掛けて\Nくれているかが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.36,0:22:30.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 考えたこともないような
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.82,0:22:35.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしいことが可能になる\Nと言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.20,0:22:39.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と友達になれるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.25,0:22:42.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と友達になるには
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.38,0:22:45.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず名前を知る必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.42,0:22:49.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はその名前を教えてくれています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:52.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバという名を持つあなただけが
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.72,0:22:57.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球全体を治める至高者である」\Nと言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:03.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして こう約束してくれています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.52,0:23:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神に近づいてください
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:09.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば\N神は近づいてくださいます」
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.28,0:23:12.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,優しいお父さんエホバは
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.53,0:23:17.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を知ろうとする人を\N喜んで友達にしてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:21.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは神の友達になりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.13,0:23:30.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことや ほかの点について\Nもっと知りたい方は
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.59,0:23:34.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.orgをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:41.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても興味深いビデオでした
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.85,0:23:46.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたも神について\N知りたいと思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.19,0:23:48.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたも呼び掛けに応じ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.57,0:23:52.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になるために\N頑張ってみたいと思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.95,0:23:58.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書には そのために必要な\Nアドバイスが書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.37,0:24:01.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書のアドバイスに従うなら
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.25,0:24:03.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来 幸せになれます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.96,0:24:05.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.00,0:24:08.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も幸せになれます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:11.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの友達になるなら今
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.84,0:24:15.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和で幸せな生活ができるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.68,0:24:17.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.72,0:24:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はあなたの祈りを聞き\N憐れみを示してくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:24.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪が許されていることを知ると
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.36,0:24:27.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,深い喜びを味わえます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.28,0:24:30.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 32:1, 2にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.95,0:24:35.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,「違反を許され\N罪を覆われる人は幸せだ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.70,0:24:40.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから罪があると\N見なされない人⋯⋯は幸せだ」
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.12,0:24:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに許してもらえるのは\N本当にうれしいことです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.92,0:24:50.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前にしてしまったことのために\N罪悪感を抱いているとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.42,0:24:52.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配は要りません
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.84,0:24:58.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を知り 神の友達になる前に\Nしてしまったことは許されます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.81,0:25:02.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたも神に許してもらうことが\Nできるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.81,0:25:07.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオにあったように 聖書を学ぶと\N神にどのように祈れるか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.52,0:25:10.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りがどのように聞かれるかが\N分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.65,0:25:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 神の許しや助けを\N求める祈りを含め
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.53,0:25:18.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が祈りを聞いてくれることを\N確信できるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.49,0:25:21.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 15:29には
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.20,0:25:24.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは「正しい人の\N祈りを聞く」とあります
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.79,0:25:26.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい人とは
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.84,0:25:31.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが求めていることに従って\N生きようと努力する人のことです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.63,0:25:35.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になれるのは\N本当にうれしいことです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.43,0:25:38.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は私たちの努力に目を留め
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.31,0:25:40.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りを聞いてくださるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.47,0:25:42.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.56,0:25:47.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になるなら\N他の人との平和な関係も楽しめます
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.31,0:25:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスも他の人と平和な関係で\Nいるよう勧めました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.07,0:25:54.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵でさえ愛するよう教え
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.74,0:25:58.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,お返しを期待せずに\N善を行うようにと言ったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.03,0:26:03.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,また ルカ 6:36では\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.25,0:26:08.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,「天の父が憐れみ深いように\N憐れみ深くありなさい」
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.79,0:26:10.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのように努力するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.92,0:26:13.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々は心を動かされ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.17,0:26:16.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分も神の友達になりたいと\N思うでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.14,0:26:21.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセという男性は\N神の友となっている人たちと接し
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.35,0:26:24.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と人を愛するようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.48,0:26:29.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセは13歳の時 ゲリラ活動に\N加わるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.27,0:26:32.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中に見られる不公正を嫌い
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.28,0:26:34.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,その原因になっていると思えた人たちを
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.65,0:26:36.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,憎むようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.16,0:26:39.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆殺しにしようと思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.78,0:26:43.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして戦いで多くの仲間が命を落とすと
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.79,0:26:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ますます怒りと復讐心に\N燃えるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.71,0:26:52.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,手りゅう弾を作りながらこう考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.26,0:26:54.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,「なぜこんなに苦しみがあるんだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.80,0:26:57.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はどうして何もしてくれないんだ？」
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.72,0:27:00.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセは何度も涙を流しました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.30,0:27:03.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,混乱し 失望しました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.60,0:27:09.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセはやがて 地元の会衆の\Nエホバの証人と出会いました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.06,0:27:14.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めて行った集会で 何て愛にあふれた\N雰囲気なんだろうと思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.40,0:27:17.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが温かく歓迎してくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.07,0:27:23.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,しばらくして 神が悪の存在を\N許しているのはなぜかについて学び
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.83,0:27:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと抱いていた疑問の\N答えが分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.21,0:27:30.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の知識が深まるにつれ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.75,0:27:33.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,考え方や生き方が変わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.84,0:27:36.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のような愛を身に着けるよう努力し
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:39.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.09,0:27:43.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 昔の仲間と関係を断つのは\N大変でした
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.14,0:27:45.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館に行くたびに
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.18,0:27:48.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔の仲間が後をつけてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.56,0:27:51.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,中には集会に出席した人もいます
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.65,0:27:56.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセがどうしてそんなに変わって\Nしまったのか知りたかったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.11,0:28:01.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて ホセが危険な存在ではない\Nことが分かり 干渉しなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.83,0:28:06.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ホセは17歳の時\Nバプテスマを受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.50,0:28:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になったホセは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.17,0:28:12.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間 伝道するようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.42,0:28:15.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を殺そうとするのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.09,0:28:19.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛と希望にあふれたメッセージを\N伝えるようになったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.43,0:28:21.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの友達になるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.93,0:28:24.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に良い結果になります
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.97,0:28:29.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前は敵だった人たちも\N互いに仲良くなり
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.73,0:28:32.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の友達になることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.73,0:28:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,まとめてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.90,0:28:40.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 神の友達になれるのはなぜか\Nということを考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.53,0:28:42.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に書かれている通り
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.58,0:28:47.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は昔 何人かの人を友と呼びました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.12,0:28:50.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が私たちとの良い関係を取り戻すため
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.46,0:28:53.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,何をしてくれたかも学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.21,0:28:57.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は子であるイエスを\N遣わしてくれたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.59,0:29:02.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ神はイエスを\N贖いの犠牲として与え
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.14,0:29:05.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを罪から解放してくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.68,0:29:11.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 神の憐れみを受け\N神の友達になるために
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.15,0:29:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉 聖書を学び
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.98,0:29:18.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の性格に倣う必要が\Nあることも学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.15,0:29:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして どうすれば今幸せな生活を送り
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.16,0:29:26.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人と平和な関係を\N持てるかも考えました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.91,0:29:33.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはご自分の友が平和な世界で\N永遠に生きられるようにしてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.25,0:29:36.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたもそこで生活したいと\N思われませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.80,0:29:43.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそうなら ぜひエホバの証人と\N聖書を学ぶようお勧めします
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.14,0:29:47.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書には 苦しみや悲しみのない世界が
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.06,0:29:50.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも続くことが約束されています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.44,0:29:54.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はご自分の友の顔から涙を拭い去り
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.40,0:29:58.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも幸せに暮らせるように\Nしてくれるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.44,0:30:01.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは単なる夢ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.70,0:30:06.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の約束は必ず実現するからです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.30,0:30:11.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございました\N神と友達になるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.60,0:30:14.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和に暮らせることが分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.85,0:30:18.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 平和を愛する多くの人が
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.61,0:30:22.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と聖書に信仰を\N持つようになっています
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.65,0:30:26.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,お望みであれば 聖書を\N無料で学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.49,0:30:29.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間と場所はご都合に合わせられます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.70,0:30:32.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人にお尋ねになるか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.41,0:30:37.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.orgから聖書レッスンを\Nお申し込みください
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.71,0:30:42.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,お近くのエホバの証人が\N喜んでお手伝いします
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.63,0:30:45.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,言語によっては jw.orgに
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.93,0:30:51.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,自習形式のオンライン聖書講座も\N用意されています
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.10,0:30:55.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,これで 3日目午前の部を終了します
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.19,0:30:58.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の部ではドラマを\N楽しむことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.23,0:31:03.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバは平和へと導いてくださる」\Nというドラマの第2部です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.99,0:31:08.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 大会最後の話をお聞きします
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.16,0:31:13.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神の約束に対する\N確信を強める歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.20,0:31:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒に歌うのは147番の歌です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.04,0:31:21.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は「約束された永遠の命」です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.38,0:31:24.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌は147番です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.09,0:31:28.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 それぞれの場所で\N祈りを捧げてください
